pages.push(
  ['gameplay-systems','Nivalis Nights Gameplay Systems','Overview of the confirmed daily life, business, ingredient, meal, fishing, boat, home, relationship, minigame, curfew and story systems.','Nivalis Nights combines a daily life simulation with business management, relationships and a persistent cyberpunk city. Players choose how to spend time rather than following one fixed career path.',[
    ['Core progression loops','The player can grow from a noodle stand into restaurants and nightclubs, buy or cultivate ingredients, manage staff activity and compete with rivals. Outside business, confirmed activities include fishing, boat exploration, home decoration, character relationships and a chess tournament.'],
    ['A persistent city','Thousands of NPCs retain schedules across districts and more than 10,000 objects preserve world state. Time of day, realistic weather, curfew security and player choices connect the simulation to story and risk. Exact formulas and unlock orders require release-build evidence.']]],
  ['business-guide','Nivalis Nights Business Strategy Guide','Spoiler-safe overview of the confirmed business ladder, ingredients, meals, staff, rivals, curfew and launch-day testing priorities.','Start with the confirmed business ladder: a noodle stand can lead toward ramen bars, restaurants and nightclubs. Ingredient supply, staffing, time and competitor risk are the key systems to test.',[
    ['Build the supply chain','More than 240 ingredients and 190 meals connect to the food-business layer. Players can buy or grow ingredients, while persistent staff actions can continue across the city. A strong strategy compares ingredient cost, menu value, labor and operating time together.'],
    ['Treat rankings as testable claims','Pre-release material does not reveal startup prices, margins or upgrade effects. After launch, “best business” guides should use controlled operating periods and include purchase cost, staffing, travel, unlock quests and curfew risk rather than ranking venues by their place in marketing copy.']]],
  ['release-date','Nivalis Nights Release Date','Nivalis Nights releases for PC on Steam on September 29, 2026. Check the confirmed date, developer and publisher details.','Nivalis Nights is scheduled to release on Steam on September 29, 2026. It is developed by ION LANDS and published by 505 Games.',[
    ['The confirmed date','The official Steam listing shows September 29, 2026 as both the release date and planned unlock date. ION LANDS also announced that date with the June 2026 name change from Nivalis to Nivalis Nights, clarifying that this is the same game with a new title and logo.'],
    ['What players should do','Wishlist the game on Steam to receive the platform notification. The current listing is for Windows PC; an official release-date trailer says the Epic Games Store version will arrive later, without giving a separate date. This page should be rechecked if either storefront changes.']]],
  ['system-requirements','Nivalis Nights System Requirements','Official minimum and recommended PC requirements for RAM, GPU memory, storage, DirectX, OS and input.','Minimum requirements include 16 GB RAM, a dedicated GPU with at least 6 GB VRAM and 30 GB storage. Recommended graphics use 8 GB VRAM, such as an RTX 2070 or newer, plus an SSD.',[
    ['Minimum PC specification','Steam lists 64-bit Windows 10 or 11, an AMD or Intel CPU, 16 GB RAM, an AMD or NVIDIA dedicated graphics card with at least 6 GB dedicated VRAM, DirectX 11, broadband internet and 30 GB available storage. Controller or keyboard and mouse input is listed.'],
    ['Recommended PC specification','The recommended listing keeps 16 GB RAM and 30 GB storage but calls for an 8 GB dedicated GPU, giving RTX 2070 or newer as an example, DirectX 12 and an SSD. The CPU line is not model-specific, so exact frame-rate predictions would be unreliable before independent benchmarks.']]],
  ['platforms','Nivalis Nights Platforms','Current Nivalis Nights platform status for Steam, Epic Games Store, consoles and Steam Deck.','The confirmed dated release is Windows PC via Steam on September 29, 2026. The official trailer says Epic Games Store will follow later. Console versions are not confirmed on the current official Steam listing.',[
    ['PC storefronts','Steam has the active product page, release date, requirements, languages and feature badges. Epic Games Store is announced for a later date, but no dated Epic page is cited in the current official release material.'],
    ['Console and handheld status','Do not treat PlayStation, Xbox or Nintendo pages from third parties as confirmation unless ION LANDS or 505 Games announces them. Steam lists controller input in the requirements, but controller support and a Valve Steam Deck compatibility rating are different questions.']]],
  ['steam-deck-controller','Nivalis Nights Steam Deck and Controller','Current controller input and Steam Deck verification status for Nivalis Nights.','The PC requirements state “Controller or keyboard + mouse.” The current Steam listing does not display a Valve Verified or Playable rating in the information reviewed for this guide.',[
    ['Controller answer','Both minimum and recommended notes mention controller or keyboard and mouse, so controller input is planned. The storefront does not expose the final button layout, remapping options or whether gameplay can be completed without switching to a pointer.'],
    ['Steam Deck answer','Controller input alone does not prove Steam Deck compatibility. A useful Deck verdict requires Valve’s rating or release-build tests covering performance, text size, launcher behavior, input prompts and battery life. Until then, this page avoids a Verified claim.']]],
  ['languages','Nivalis Nights Languages','The 11 languages listed for Nivalis Nights, with interface, subtitles and English full-audio status.','Steam lists English plus ten translated languages. English includes full audio; all listed languages include interface and subtitles.',[
    ['Complete list','The current storefront lists English, French, German, Spanish from Spain, Japanese, Korean, Brazilian Portuguese, Russian, Simplified Chinese, Traditional Chinese and Turkish. The May developer update says three QA teams and dedicated localization testing are involved.'],
    ['Asian-language support','ION LANDS specifically describes preparing optimized fonts for Chinese, Korean and Japanese before translation updates. Store fields can change close to release, so players looking for a particular dub should distinguish full audio from translated interface and subtitle support.']]],
  ['demo-guide','Does Nivalis Nights Have a Demo?','Current Nivalis Nights demo availability and how to verify any future demo or save transfer support.','The official Steam store page reviewed on July 17, 2026 does not list a downloadable public demo. Wishlist or follow the game for any later announcement.',[
    ['Current status','The product page says the game is not yet available and offers the wishlist action. A demo button or demo package is not shown in the official listing reviewed for this update. This is a current-status answer, not a claim that a demo can never appear.'],
    ['Save transfer','Because no current public demo is listed, there is no official demo-to-full-game save transfer promise to document. If a demo appears, its own announcement or FAQ should be the source for progress limits, availability window and transfer behavior.']]],
  ['price-editions','Nivalis Nights Price and Editions','Current price and edition status for Nivalis Nights on Steam.','The official Steam page reviewed on July 17, 2026 does not display a launch price or multiple editions. The actionable option before release is to wishlist the game.',[
    ['Price status','The storefront provides the date, features, supported languages and PC requirements, but the pre-release purchase box does not yet show a price. Regional launch prices and discounts should not be inferred from third-party key listings.'],
    ['Edition status','No standard-versus-deluxe comparison is available from the official page reviewed here. If 505 Games announces editions, this page should compare included content, cosmetic versus gameplay items, price difference and upgrade paths using the official product details.']]],
  ['fishing-guide','Nivalis Nights Fishing Guide','How fishing works in Nivalis Nights, including visible fish simulation, shoal behavior, bait response and boat exploration.','Fishing is not a hidden random roll. Fish have physical representations, form shoals, react to bait and can be seen in the water before being caught.',[
    ['Physical fish simulation','ION LANDS says hundreds of fish can appear simultaneously and more than 1,000 can be simulated. Each follows other fish or bait, so the salmon a player catches is the same one previously visible in the water. Fish also emit a warm glow.'],
    ['Locations, bait and values','Exact species lists, fishing spots, bait preferences, time windows and sell values are not public in the cited developer update. Those details need release-build testing. The official feature list does confirm that the player can explore by personal boat and go fishing.']]],
  ['romance-guide','Nivalis Nights Romance and Dating Guide','What is confirmed about romance, friendships, enemies and character relationships in Nivalis Nights.','Romance is part of the game: official copy says players may find love, while the broader system includes friendships, enemies and relationship management.',[
    ['Relationship scope','The game asks players to choose between growing a business and forging bonds with inhabitants. Character stories, quests, rewards and choices are designed to interconnect, so relationship guides should cover more than gift lists.'],
    ['No invented romance options','The official material reviewed here does not publish a complete romanceable-character roster, gift preferences or event requirements. Those details will be added by named character only after official confirmation or release-build verification, with spoilers labelled.']]],
  ['money-guide','Nivalis Nights Money and Business Guide','Confirmed ways the Nivalis Nights economy connects businesses, ingredients, meals, fishing and competitors.','The primary announced economic route starts with a noodle stand and grows toward ramen bars, restaurants and nightclubs. Fishing and ingredient supply support the wider life-sim loop.',[
    ['Starting small','Official descriptions repeatedly say the player begins humbly with a noodle or food stand. Players can buy or grow ingredients and spend their days expanding businesses. Exact starting cash, prices and profit margins are not yet public.'],
    ['Reinvestment and risk','The business layer includes staff activity, competitors and illegal sabotage under curfew. A reliable “fastest money” route requires comparable release-build tests of startup cost, operating time, ingredient cost, staffing and upgrades rather than assumptions from the business order.']]],
  ['apartment-decorating','Nivalis Nights Apartments and Decorating','Confirmed home ownership, decoration and furniture systems in Nivalis Nights.','Players can buy and decorate apartments or homes, and can also customize homes for friends. The game includes 620 furniture items according to ION LANDS.',[
    ['Home customization','The official Steam copy treats home decoration as a major low-pressure activity alongside boating, fishing and chess. It refers to multiple homes and customization for friends, although purchase prices and ownership limits are not yet public.'],
    ['Persistent furniture','Developer technology notes describe more than 10,000 persistent world elements, including tables, chairs and dishes, and a major furniture asset polish. Individual item pages need verified acquisition, cost, category and placement details before indexing.']]],
  ['city-guide','Nivalis Nights City and District Guide','Confirmed information about the cyberpunk city of Nivalis, its districts, docks, security and persistent population.','Nivalis is a cyberpunk city stretching from the ocean to the clouds, with districts, docks, businesses, homes, persistent NPC schedules and a realistic weather system.',[
    ['A dense simulated city','ION LANDS says thousands of NPCs continue living their lives. The engine tracks distant district schedules, nearby unseen residents and fully visible characters differently, while more than 10,000 world objects retain their state.'],
    ['Navigation and danger','Players can explore by their own boat, visit docks and move through a district under CorpSec crackdowns. Curfew and security systems add risk. A complete map needs the shipped location names and routes, so this guide does not invent a district list.']]],
  ['day-night-weather','Nivalis Nights Day, Night and Weather','How daily choices, curfew and realistic weather shape the Nivalis Nights simulation.','The game has day and night cycles, a realistic weather system and curfew-related risk. Players decide how to spend each day across business, relationships and other activities.',[
    ['Time management','The official description frames each day as a choice between growing businesses and forming bonds. Steam also tags the game for time management. Exact day length, sleep rules and business opening hours are not yet public.'],
    ['Weather and curfew','The developer says rain and snow effects have been refined. At night, illegal competitor sabotage can occur under curfew, requiring players to avoid security systems. Weather-specific fishing or crop effects still require verification.']]],
  ['beginner-guide','Nivalis Nights Beginner Guide','A spoiler-safe introduction to the confirmed business, relationship, fishing, home, boat and story systems.','Begin by understanding the daily-choice loop: business growth and ingredient supply compete for time with relationships, fishing, boating, decorating and story progress.',[
    ['Choose a focus, not a fantasy build','The official systems suggest several connected paths rather than fixed classes. A noodle stand can lead into larger food and nightlife businesses, while relationships and quests are designed to interact with rewards and the economy.'],
    ['What not to over-plan','Exact profit rankings, best gifts, fish schedules and quest routes are not public before release. Check PC requirements, choose an input method, wishlist the game and use broad system knowledge until tested launch data supports optimization.']]],
  ['best-tips','Nivalis Nights Tips','Useful spoiler-free pre-release tips grounded in confirmed Nivalis Nights systems.','Treat time, ingredient supply and relationships as connected resources. The game lets you specialize, but official descriptions emphasize that daily choices influence business and character progress.',[
    ['Plan around connected systems','Growing ingredients can support food businesses; boating connects exploration and fishing; homes use a large furniture collection; curfew can turn business rivalry into risk. Avoid assuming each activity exists in isolation.'],
    ['Wait for tested rankings','Before release there is no reliable evidence for the best meal, fish, business or upgrade. Once the game launches, comparisons should use consistent time periods and include startup costs, staffing, travel and unlock requirements.']]],
  ['known-issues','Nivalis Nights Known Issues and Patch Notes','Current pre-release issue status and the future versioned troubleshooting policy.','Nivalis Nights has not released yet, so there is no public launch-build issue list. ION LANDS says it is optimizing performance and testing stability, saves, quests, UI, localization and compatibility.',[
    ['Pre-release optimization work','The May update details LODs, light-probe optimization, NPC object pooling, reduced allocations and loading improvements. QA teams test general stability, save/load, quest progression, environments, characters, UI, memory and performance.'],
    ['How issues will be documented','After launch, each issue needs a game version, affected platform or hardware, reproduction steps, workaround and official status. Old workarounds must remain tied to their version so fixed problems do not continue ranking as current advice.']]],
  ['checklists','Nivalis Nights Checklists','Spoiler-safe preparation and launch verification checklists for players and completionists.','Before launch, check the date, PC requirements, language and input support. After launch, collection checklists will cover only verified quests, ingredients, meals, furniture and other entities.',[
    ['Pre-release checklist','Confirm Windows 10/11 64-bit, 16 GB RAM, dedicated GPU memory and 30 GB free space; prefer an SSD for the recommended setup. Check that your chosen language and input method are listed, then wishlist the Steam release.'],
    ['Completion checklist policy','The developers report 100+ quests, 240+ ingredients, 190 meals and 620 furniture items. Those counts justify future checklists, but completion percentages require exact release-build inventories rather than empty boxes or invented names.']]],
  ['faq','Nivalis Nights FAQ','Quick answers about the release date, platform, game type, businesses, fishing, romance, languages and PC requirements.','Nivalis Nights is a single-player cyberpunk life sim releasing on Steam on September 29, 2026, with business management, relationships, fishing, boating, homes, minigames and story choices.',[
    ['Who makes Nivalis Nights?','ION LANDS develops the game and 505 Games publishes it. It was previously promoted as Nivalis; the developer says Nivalis Nights is the same game with a new title and logo.'],
    ['When does Nivalis Nights release?','The Steam version is scheduled for September 29, 2026. Epic Games Store is also announced for Windows in 2026, but its store page does not currently provide the same specific date.'],
    ['Which platforms are confirmed?','Windows PC is confirmed through Steam and Epic Games Store. No PlayStation, Xbox, Nintendo Switch, native macOS or native Linux version currently appears in the official platform listings.'],
    ['What are the PC requirements?','Steam lists 16 GB RAM, 30 GB storage and at least 6 GB dedicated VRAM for minimum. Recommended graphics call for 8 GB VRAM, such as an RTX 2070 or newer, plus DirectX 12 and an SSD.'],
    ['How many characters are there?','ION LANDS says there are more than 130 authored characters with goals, backgrounds and personalities. The city separately simulates thousands of ambient NPCs with daily schedules.'],
    ['How large is the item and quest content?','A May 2026 development update reports more than 100 quests, over 240 ingredients, 190 meals and 620 furniture items. Individual database pages publish only after exact details are verifiable.']],round2Date],
  ['nivalis-vs-nivalis-nights','Nivalis vs Nivalis Nights','Why the game formerly called Nivalis is now named Nivalis Nights.','Nivalis Nights is the same ION LANDS game previously called Nivalis. The developer announced the new title and logo on June 30, 2026 after resolving a legal matter.',[
    ['What changed','ION LANDS says marketing had been paused while it handled a legal matter with a third party. Once resolved, the team announced the fresh title, logo and September 29, 2026 release date. The underlying game did not become a sequel or separate project.'],
    ['How to read older information','Older trailers, store links and discussions may still use Nivalis. They can remain relevant when they refer to Steam app 1488490 or the same ION LANDS project, but dates and features should be rechecked against current official pages.']]],
  ['about','About Nivalis Nights Wiki','Editorial standards, sourcing and independence information for Nivalis Nights Wiki.','Nivalis Nights Wiki is an independent, unofficial English player resource. It is not affiliated with ION LANDS or 505 Games.',[
    ['Editorial policy','Pre-release claims are sourced to official storefronts and developer updates. After release, exact guides can also use reproducible first-hand testing. Speculation, placeholder entity pages and fabricated names are excluded from the sitemap.'],
    ['Corrections and spoilers','Time-sensitive answers show a review date. Story choices and endings receive spoiler warnings, while corrections should update both the page and its source record. Trademarks and game assets remain the property of their respective owners.']]]
);

pages.push(
  ['ram-requirement','How Much RAM Does Nivalis Nights Need?','Official minimum and recommended memory requirements for Nivalis Nights on PC.','Nivalis Nights requires 16 GB RAM in both the minimum and recommended Steam specifications.',[
    ['Minimum and recommended memory','Unlike games that list separate memory tiers, the current Steam page uses 16 GB for both. Meeting that number does not guarantee recommended performance because GPU memory, DirectX support and storage type also differ between tiers.'],
    ['Why the game may use memory','ION LANDS describes thousands of scheduled NPCs, more than 10,000 persistent objects and hundreds of content entries. The team has optimized object pooling, light probes and allocations to manage that dense simulation.'],
    ['Upgrade decision','A computer with 8 GB system RAM is below the current official minimum. Players should compare the complete specification rather than treating a 16 GB upgrade as the only requirement.']],round2Date],
  ['storage-size','Nivalis Nights Download and Storage Size','How much free storage Nivalis Nights requires and what is known about final download size.','Steam lists 30 GB of available storage for both minimum and recommended PC setups. That is a free-space requirement, not a confirmed final download size.',[
    ['Official storage figure','The current Steam requirements use 30 GB in both tiers. Installation size can differ from compressed download size, and patches may change the final footprint.'],
    ['SSD recommendation','An SSD is included in the recommended notes but not the minimum notes. The developer has worked on loading, memory allocations and district transitions, all of which are relevant to storage performance.'],
    ['Launch-day check','The guide will update with installed size and patch overhead from the release build rather than converting the 30 GB requirement into an invented download estimate.']],round2Date],
  ['ssd-requirement','Does Nivalis Nights Require an SSD?','Whether an SSD is required or recommended for Nivalis Nights on PC.','An SSD is recommended, but it is not listed as mandatory in the minimum Steam requirements. Both tiers require 30 GB of free storage.',[
    ['Minimum versus recommended','The minimum notes do not specify drive type. The recommended notes explicitly add an SSD, so a hard drive may meet the written minimum while offering a worse loading experience.'],
    ['Why storage speed may matter','The city uses loading screens between large districts and dynamically materializes NPCs as they approach the player. ION LANDS has specifically optimized loading time and object pooling.'],
    ['No invented loading times','Exact HDD and SSD comparisons require the shipped build on comparable hardware. This page does not promise a target loading time before those tests exist.']],round2Date],
  ['vram-requirement','How Much VRAM Does Nivalis Nights Need?','Official minimum and recommended dedicated graphics memory requirements.','Nivalis Nights requires a dedicated AMD or NVIDIA graphics card with at least 6 GB VRAM. The recommended tier calls for 8 GB dedicated VRAM.',[
    ['Minimum graphics memory','The Steam minimum specifies a dedicated GPU with 6 GB VRAM and DirectX 11. Integrated graphics are not listed as a supported substitute.'],
    ['Recommended graphics memory','The recommended tier raises graphics memory to 8 GB and gives an RTX 2070 or newer as an example, alongside DirectX 12.'],
    ['Visual workload','The voxel-built city uses high polygon counts, multiple levels of detail, vegetation, lighting probes and weather effects. Actual resolution and quality presets still need benchmarks.']],round2Date],
  ['rtx-2070-performance','Can an RTX 2070 Run Nivalis Nights?','How the RTX 2070 appears in the official recommended Nivalis Nights specification.','Yes. Steam gives “RTX 2070 or newer” as an example for the recommended graphics tier, which also specifies 8 GB dedicated VRAM and DirectX 12.',[
    ['What recommended means','The listing does not attach a resolution, frame rate or quality preset to the RTX 2070 example. It confirms the card class but not a 60 FPS guarantee at a particular setting.'],
    ['Other required components','The recommended setup also lists 16 GB RAM, Windows 10 or 11 64-bit, 30 GB storage and an SSD. The CPU requirement remains generic rather than naming a model.'],
    ['Benchmark policy','Release tests should report resolution, preset, district, weather and crowd conditions. An average frame rate without those details would be misleading.']],round2Date],
  ['directx-requirement','Nivalis Nights DirectX 11 and DirectX 12 Requirements','Which DirectX version is needed for minimum and recommended PC setups.','The minimum specification lists DirectX 11. The recommended specification lists DirectX 12.',[
    ['Minimum API','Players targeting the minimum tier need a compatible dedicated GPU with at least 6 GB VRAM alongside DirectX 11 and 64-bit Windows 10 or 11.'],
    ['Recommended API','DirectX 12 belongs to the recommended tier, together with 8 GB dedicated VRAM, an RTX 2070-or-newer example and SSD storage.'],
    ['Do not infer performance','The store page does not describe feature-level requirements or the performance difference between the two render paths. Those questions need release-build testing.']],round2Date],
  ['windows-requirement','Nivalis Nights Windows 10 and Windows 11 Support','Which Windows versions and architecture are listed for Nivalis Nights.','Nivalis Nights supports 64-bit Windows 10 and Windows 11 according to both the minimum and recommended Steam requirements.',[
    ['64-bit requirement','The store page explicitly requires a 64-bit processor and operating system. A 32-bit Windows installation is therefore outside the listed specification.'],
    ['Windows 7 status','The current Steam page does not include Windows 7. Older storefront information can show outdated requirements, so the renamed game’s current Steam listing should be treated as the source of truth.'],
    ['Other operating systems','macOS and Linux are not listed on the current Steam requirements. Separate platform pages track those statuses without assuming compatibility through Proton or virtualization.']],round2Date],
  ['aspect-ratio-support','Nivalis Nights Aspect Ratio and 4:3 UI Support','What ION LANDS has said about 4:3 and other display aspect ratios.','ION LANDS says the user interface was designed to support multiple screen aspect ratios, explicitly including 4:3.',[
    ['Responsive interface','The game contains more than 40 windows, panels and interface elements. The optimization goal is to keep them clear and consistent across display configurations.'],
    ['What is not confirmed','Support for 4:3 does not by itself confirm ultrawide field of view, multi-monitor behavior, resolution lists or cutscene presentation. Those need settings-menu and gameplay tests.'],
    ['Launch checks','The final display guide will compare HUD scaling, text readability, letterboxing and field of view at common 16:9, 16:10, 21:9 and 4:3 ratios.']],round2Date],
  ['epic-games-store','Nivalis Nights Epic Games Store Release','Current Epic Games Store availability and how its timing compares with the Steam release.','Nivalis Nights has an official Epic Games Store page and is listed as coming to Windows in 2026. The dated September 29, 2026 launch is currently confirmed on Steam; the release trailer says Epic will follow later.',[
    ['Epic availability','The publisher page shows both Steam and Epic as platforms, and Epic has a wishlist page for the game. The Epic listing still uses some older Nivalis branding and information.'],
    ['Do not reuse old specifications','Older Epic requirement fields differ from the current Steam requirements. This wiki uses the current Steam PC specification rather than presenting the older Epic numbers as launch requirements.'],
    ['Date status','Until Epic or 505 Games provides a specific day, the Epic version should be described as 2026 or later than Steam, not automatically assigned the September 29 date.']],round2Date],
  ['ps5-release','Is Nivalis Nights Coming to PS5?','Current PlayStation 5 release status for Nivalis Nights.','No PS5 version has been announced by ION LANDS or 505 Games in the current official platform listings. The confirmed platforms are Windows storefronts on Steam and Epic Games Store.',[
    ['Current official listings','Steam provides the dated September 29, 2026 Windows release. The publisher page shows Steam and Epic logos but does not show PlayStation.'],
    ['What controller support means','The PC requirements mention controller input, but that is not evidence of a console port. A PS5 page, trailer or publisher platform badge would be needed for confirmation.'],
    ['Update rule','This status page will change only after an official announcement. Store wish lists, retailer placeholders or fan requests are not platform confirmation.']],round2Date],
  ['xbox-release','Is Nivalis Nights Coming to Xbox?','Current Xbox Series X|S and Xbox One release status for Nivalis Nights.','No Xbox version is currently announced in the official Nivalis Nights platform listings. Steam and Epic Games Store on Windows are the confirmed storefronts.',[
    ['No Xbox badge','The official 505 Games game page shows platform icons for Steam and Epic, unlike other publisher pages that explicitly display Xbox when a version exists.'],
    ['Single-player and cloud badges','Steam Cloud and single-player support are Steam features; they do not indicate Xbox cloud saves, Play Anywhere or Game Pass availability.'],
    ['Evidence needed','An ION LANDS announcement, Xbox store listing or 505 Games platform update would be required before this page marks an Xbox release as confirmed.']],round2Date],
  ['switch-release','Is Nivalis Nights Coming to Nintendo Switch?','Current Nintendo Switch and Switch 2 release status for Nivalis Nights.','No Nintendo Switch or Switch 2 version is currently announced by the developer or publisher. Official platform pages presently identify Windows via Steam and Epic.',[
    ['Current status','Neither the current Steam listing nor the 505 Games Nivalis page displays a Nintendo platform badge. The game’s controller input support does not establish a Switch port.'],
    ['Hardware considerations are not evidence','PC requirements call for 16 GB RAM and a dedicated GPU, but those specifications cannot be used to prove or disprove a custom console version. Only an official announcement can.'],
    ['Avoid placeholder stores','Unverified retailer pages and search snippets will not be treated as confirmation. This page will update if Nintendo, ION LANDS or 505 Games publishes a listing.']],round2Date],
  ['mac-support','Is Nivalis Nights Available on Mac?','Current macOS support status for Nivalis Nights.','No native macOS version is listed on the current official Steam or Epic Games Store pages. The published requirements specify 64-bit Windows.',[
    ['Windows is the listed OS','Steam names Windows 10 and Windows 11 in both requirement tiers. The Epic listing also identifies Windows as its platform.'],
    ['No compatibility promise','Running through translation, streaming or virtualization is different from native support and is not guaranteed by the developer. This page does not present those workarounds as an official Mac version.'],
    ['What would confirm support','A macOS store badge, system-requirement tab or developer announcement is needed before the status changes.']],round2Date],
  ['linux-support','Is Nivalis Nights Available on Linux?','Current native Linux and SteamOS support status for Nivalis Nights.','No native Linux version is listed in the current official system requirements. Steam currently specifies 64-bit Windows 10 or 11.',[
    ['Native support status','The absence of Linux from the OS list means it should not be marketed as a native Linux release. The Epic page likewise lists Windows.'],
    ['Proton is a separate question','Community compatibility through Proton may be tested after release, but it is not equivalent to a developer-supported Linux build or a Valve Steam Deck rating.'],
    ['Launch verification','Any Proton guide must record version, hardware, launch options, video playback, controller behavior and save compatibility before becoming indexable.']],round2Date]
);

pages.push(
  ['core-gameplay-loop','Nivalis Nights Core Gameplay Loop','How quests, relationships, restaurant management and daily choices form the main Nivalis Nights gameplay loop.','The core loop combines story quests and relationships with restaurant management. During each day, players decide how much time to spend following the story and how much to invest in ingredients, staff, venue upgrades and expansion.',[
    ['Story and people come first','ION LANDS describes Nivalis Nights as a combination of narrative, life simulation and management. Players follow quests across the city, uncover connected stories and build relationships with major characters rather than operating businesses in a separate menu-only layer.'],
    ['The management half','Business play includes buying ingredients, upgrading a venue, hiring and managing staff and expanding into new districts. Fishing, greenhouses and recipe unlocks feed into that economy, while apartments, boating and minigames provide other ways to spend time.'],
    ['What varies by player','The story has a destination, but the route is flexible. The balance between business growth, character side quests and exploration depends on daily decisions, which is why a single mandatory “best schedule” cannot be confirmed before release.']],round2Date],
  ['main-story-ending','Does Nivalis Nights Have a Main Story and Ending?','Whether Nivalis Nights has a defined story, a specific ending and activities that continue over time.','Yes. The developer says Nivalis Nights has a defined story with a beginning and a specific ending, although players can take many different paths and some simulation systems can continue over time.',[
    ['Not an endless sandbox only','The life-sim and management systems do not replace the narrative. Players spend substantial time following quests, investigating the plot and meeting main characters, and the team has balanced major story beats with quest rewards and the game economy.'],
    ['Different paths to the destination','Character choices and side quests can produce different dialogue and outcomes. The statement that there is a specific ending does not establish how many variants, endings or post-game states exist; those details require the finished game.'],
    ['Spoiler policy','Story walkthroughs will keep the ending out of titles and meta descriptions. Decision pages will show requirements first and hide consequences behind clear spoiler warnings.']],round2Date],
  ['side-quests','Nivalis Nights Side Quests','How side quests connect to more than 130 characters, relationships, dialogue outcomes and main progression.','Side quests are a major part of Nivalis Nights. ION LANDS says the game has more than 130 characters, each with goals, background and personality, and player interactions can lead to different dialogue and outcomes.',[
    ['Character-driven quest design','Relationships can develop as friendship, rivalry, business partnership or romance. Side quests tied to those characters are one of the main ways choices change how an inhabitant interacts with the player.'],
    ['Progression and rewards','The development team says story beats link to gameplay systems and offer rewards. Quest difficulty, pacing and the economy have been balanced together, so side content should not be treated as flavor text without progression value.'],
    ['Walkthrough standard','After release, each quest page needs exact prerequisites, steps, locations, choices, rewards and failure or trigger notes. The character count alone will never be used to create empty quest URLs.']],round2Date],
  ['characters-count','How Many Characters Are in Nivalis Nights?','The confirmed Nivalis Nights character count and how NPC schedules differ from named story characters.','ION LANDS says Nivalis Nights has more than 130 characters with their own goals, backgrounds and personalities. The city also simulates thousands of ambient NPCs, but those are not the same as 130+ authored characters.',[
    ['Authored characters','The confirmed 130+ figure comes from the developer’s community Q&A about side quests. Choices can change dialogue and outcomes, and relationship types include friendship, rivalry, business partnership and romance.'],
    ['Simulated population','A separate optimization update describes thousands of NPCs following daily schedules through a tiered Ghost system. That larger population makes the city feel alive, but only named characters with meaningful roles should receive database pages.'],
    ['Database target','The character hub will grow toward the confirmed authored cast after names and roles are verifiable. Each leaf page must provide location, schedule or quest connections rather than merely restating a name.']],round2Date],
  ['salt-pete','Salt Pete Character Guide','Who Salt Pete is, where he works and what the developer has revealed about the Nivalis Nights robot ferryman.','Salt Pete is a tall robot ferryman found near the docks. He operates a makeshift ferry across the bay, wears a straw hat and has a cheerful but argumentative personality.',[
    ['Where to find Salt Pete','ION LANDS introduced him in a May 2025 character spotlight. He works around the docks and offers a cheap crossing on a vessel assembled from riveted sheet metal, although his own joking safety claim is not a reliable success statistic.'],
    ['Personality and relationships','Salt Pete enjoys hearing passengers’ stories but avoids discussing his own past. He bickers with other harbor robots, including one called Caleb, and may involve the player in that ongoing conflict.'],
    ['Guide status','His exact schedule, fares, connected quests and relationship outcomes are not yet public. Those fields will be added only after official disclosure or release-build verification.']],round2Date],
  ['greenhouses','Nivalis Nights Greenhouse Guide','How greenhouse rental, crop growing, equipment, skills and restaurant supply work in Nivalis Nights.','Players can rent and manage multiple high-tech greenhouses around Nivalis. They can equip and customize them, grow crops from seeds and either sell the harvest or use it as restaurant inventory.',[
    ['Why farming uses greenhouses','Open land is scarce in the industrial city, so farming is placed inside high-tech structures across the map. Players with enough money can rent more than one greenhouse and expand as their farming skills and seed access improve.'],
    ['Equipment and progression','Specialized machinery comes from different city vendors. Advanced modules unlock over time, while the farming console controls growing conditions and some processes such as irrigation can be automated.'],
    ['Business connection','Harvested crops can be sold directly or moved into restaurant supply. The developer specifically positions greenhouse production as a way to reduce pressure and improve profits when restaurant management becomes more demanding.']],round2Date],
  ['greenhouse-crops','Nivalis Nights Crops and Seeds','Confirmed greenhouse crop categories, seed requirements and uses for harvested ingredients.','Confirmed greenhouse outputs include mushrooms, grains and vegetables, while more advanced equipment can even print meat. Crops require the necessary seeds and can be sold or used in restaurants.',[
    ['Known crop categories','ION LANDS has named mushrooms, grains and vegetables as examples rather than publishing the complete crop list. This page therefore groups confirmed categories without inventing individual plant names or growth times.'],
    ['Seeds and skills','Players acquire seeds and unlock more options over time with the right skills. Multiple greenhouses can be rented, allowing production to expand beyond one small plot.'],
    ['What each crop page will need','A future crop entry must show seed source, environmental settings, growth time, yield, sale value and recipe uses. Cosmetic plant pages will not be mixed with productive crops.']],round2Date],
  ['greenhouse-automation','Nivalis Nights Greenhouse Automation','How temperature, humidity, light and automated irrigation affect greenhouse management.','Greenhouse consoles let players configure temperature, humidity and light, which directly influence crop growth speed. Irrigation is one of the processes that can be automated.',[
    ['Environmental controls','The farming console is designed for optimizing cultivation and yield. Temperature, humidity and lighting are adjustable rather than fixed background effects, giving greenhouse management its own systems layer.'],
    ['Machinery and modules','Players can install specialized machinery bought from city vendors and unlock advanced modules as farming develops. The developer has confirmed automation but has not published exact thresholds or optimal settings.'],
    ['Testing plan','Release guides should compare one variable at a time, record crop, growth duration and yield, and distinguish convenience upgrades from profit increases. Generic “best settings” claims will wait for reproducible data.']],round2Date],
  ['inventory-guide','Nivalis Nights Inventory Guide','The confirmed personal, kitchen, greenhouse and home inventories in Nivalis Nights.','Nivalis Nights uses multiple inventories: the player’s personal inventory, restaurant kitchens, rented greenhouses and homes each have their own storage context.',[
    ['Separate storage contexts','The developer’s community Q&A explicitly identifies personal, kitchen, greenhouse and home inventories. This means resource planning involves where an item is stored, not only the total quantity owned.'],
    ['Why transfers matter','Ingredients can move from buying or greenhouse production into restaurant use, while harvested goods can also be sold. Exact transfer rules, remote access and stack limits are not yet public and should not be assumed.'],
    ['Launch guide fields','The completed guide will document capacity, sorting, filters, item movement, storage upgrades and whether staff can access kitchen stock automatically.']],round2Date],
  ['transportation','Nivalis Nights Transportation Guide','How HOVA taxis, trains and player-controlled boats move players between and within districts.','Players travel between districts using automated HOVA taxis and trains. Cars cannot be driven, but the player can pilot a personal boat to explore waterways and reach connected areas.',[
    ['Inter-district travel','Nivalis is divided into large districts, and automated transportation handles movement between them. The developer confirms loading screens during district changes.'],
    ['Water travel','The player’s boat is the directly controllable vehicle confirmed so far. It supports exploration, reaches water-connected areas and expands fishing by opening new spots and species.'],
    ['What is not established','Fares, station maps, schedules and fast-travel unlock rules have not been published. These need route testing in the final build.']],round2Date],
  ['can-you-drive-cars','Can You Drive Cars in Nivalis Nights?','Whether cars are drivable and which vehicles players can control in Nivalis Nights.','No. ION LANDS says players will not be able to drive cars. District travel uses HOVA taxis and trains, while the player can directly pilot a boat.',[
    ['How road travel works','The Q&A describes HOVA taxis and trains as automated systems used to move between districts. That makes them transportation services rather than player-driven vehicles.'],
    ['The controllable alternative','Boats provide the confirmed hands-on vehicle system. They enable freer exploration of the waters around Nivalis and help players reach additional fishing areas.'],
    ['Scope of the answer','This answer reflects the developer’s explicit pre-release statement. It does not infer motorcycles, bicycles or other unannounced vehicle types.']],round2Date],
  ['hova-taxis','Nivalis Nights HOVA Taxi Guide','What HOVA taxis do and how they fit Nivalis Nights district travel.','HOVA taxis are an automated transportation option for moving between Nivalis districts. Players cannot drive cars themselves.',[
    ['Confirmed role','ION LANDS groups HOVA taxis with trains as the systems used for inter-district travel. The city’s large districts are freely explored once entered, but changing districts includes a loading screen.'],
    ['Information still needed','The developer has not published taxi fares, pickup points, route restrictions or unlock conditions. A release guide will map stops and compare travel time with trains and boat routes.'],
    ['Cloudpunk context','HOVAs are familiar technology in the city of Nivalis, which also appeared in Cloudpunk. Nivalis Nights is nevertheless designed to work as a standalone game.']],round2Date],
  ['trains','Nivalis Nights Train Guide','How trains are used for inter-district travel in Nivalis Nights.','Trains are one of the automated systems that move players between the city’s large districts, alongside HOVA taxis.',[
    ['District connections','The developer confirms that district changes use transportation and include loading screens. Within an entered district, players can move freely and explore most business interiors.'],
    ['What is not public','Station names, lines, fares, schedules and late-night restrictions have not been detailed. The final guide will need an actual route map and access conditions.'],
    ['Other travel options','Players cannot drive cars, but they can pilot their own boat for water-connected areas. Trains should therefore be documented as one part of a mixed travel network.']],round2Date],
  ['multiple-properties','Can You Own Multiple Properties in Nivalis Nights?','How multiple restaurants, venues, apartments and standalone houses work across Nivalis districts.','Yes. Players can purchase multiple restaurants or venues, plus apartments and standalone houses in different districts. Each district’s properties have their own style.',[
    ['Business expansion','Owning more than one restaurant or venue is part of expanding the business into new districts. Staff, ingredients and upgrades make that expansion a management problem rather than a cosmetic collection alone.'],
    ['Residential ownership','The community Q&A separately confirms apartments and standalone houses across the city. Existing official features also allow players to decorate their homes and customize spaces for friends or paying clients.'],
    ['Progression limits','Exact property counts, prices and prerequisites are not yet published. Individual property URLs will wait for verified names, locations and benefits.']],round2Date],
  ['restaurant-upgrades','Nivalis Nights Restaurant Upgrades','What restaurant upgrades are confirmed and which costs and effects need launch testing.','Venue upgrades are part of the core management loop. Players buy ingredients, upgrade their restaurant, hire staff and later expand into additional districts.',[
    ['Upgrade purpose','Restaurant growth interacts with recipes, ingredient supply, kitchen inventory and staffing. Greenhouses can reduce supply pressure, while new recipes and customization add more menu options over time.'],
    ['What has not been revealed','Official Q&A confirms the system but not an upgrade tree, prices or numerical effects. A useful guide must compare capacity, speed, menu, storage and profit changes rather than list upgrade names alone.'],
    ['Evidence standard','Each future upgrade page needs unlock requirements, cost, exact effect and whether it applies to one venue or the wider business.']],round2Date],
  ['staff-management','Nivalis Nights Staff Management','How hiring and managing restaurant staff fits the Nivalis Nights business simulation.','Players can hire and manage staff as they grow restaurant businesses. The persistent city simulation can track staff serving customers even when the player is elsewhere.',[
    ['Confirmed management role','Staffing appears in the developer’s core-loop explanation alongside ingredients, upgrades and cross-district expansion. It is therefore a progression system, not merely ambient animation.'],
    ['Persistent work','The optimization update gives an example of staff serving Nigiri to customers across the city while the player is occupied elsewhere. This supports multi-venue operations but does not reveal scheduling or payroll rules.'],
    ['Launch guide questions','The complete guide should document hiring source, roles, wages, skills, shifts, capacity and automation. “Best employee” pages require named staff and tested statistics.']],round2Date],
  ['recipe-customization','Nivalis Nights Recipe Customization','How recipe unlocks and customization connect ingredients to restaurant management.','Players unlock new recipes as they progress and can customize them, adding another decision layer to restaurant operations.',[
    ['Beyond fixed recipes','The developer distinguishes unlocking recipes from customizing them. That suggests meals are not only static collection entries, although the exact ingredient substitution or quality rules are not yet public.'],
    ['Supply connection','Ingredients can be purchased or produced in greenhouses, then stored in kitchens and used by restaurant businesses. Custom recipes should therefore be evaluated for supply cost as well as sale value.'],
    ['Future recipe tests','Each recipe page will need base ingredients, customization options, unlock source, preparation requirements and effect on customers or profit.']],round2Date],
  ['business-expansion','How to Expand Your Business in Nivalis Nights','Confirmed restaurant growth from upgrades and staff to multiple venues across city districts.','Business expansion includes upgrading a venue, hiring staff and buying multiple restaurants or other venues in additional districts.',[
    ['From one venue to a network','The official business ladder starts with small food operations and can grow into restaurants, bars and nightclubs. The Q&A confirms that ownership can spread across districts rather than ending at one upgraded location.'],
    ['Supply and delegation','Multiple inventories, greenhouse production and persistent staff activity support a networked business. The economic challenge is likely to include keeping kitchens supplied while deciding how much daily time to spend on story and relationships.'],
    ['Strategy gate','No expansion order can be ranked before prices, prerequisites and returns are tested. Release comparisons should include travel, staffing and upgrade costs.']],round2Date],
  ['cloudpunk-connection','Is Nivalis Nights Connected to Cloudpunk?','How Nivalis Nights shares its city with Cloudpunk while remaining a standalone experience.','Yes. Nivalis Nights takes place in the same city featured in ION LANDS’ earlier game Cloudpunk, and returning players may notice familiar details and small connections. It is designed to stand alone.',[
    ['Shared setting','ION LANDS directly confirms that Nivalis is the same city. Technology such as HOVA transport and the cyberpunk urban setting may feel familiar to Cloudpunk players.'],
    ['No prerequisite game','The developer also says Nivalis Nights is designed as a standalone experience. Players should not need to finish Cloudpunk to understand the main story, characters or management systems.'],
    ['Reference guide policy','Connections will be documented only when a location, character, event or object is verifiably shared. Visual resemblance alone is not enough to create a lore claim.']],round2Date],
  ['loading-screens','Does Nivalis Nights Have Loading Screens?','Where loading screens occur when exploring Nivalis districts and interiors.','Yes. ION LANDS says there are loading screens when traveling between the city’s large districts. Within each district, players can freely explore the area and most business interiors.',[
    ['District boundaries','The city is structured as several large, detailed districts rather than one continuously loaded map. HOVA taxis and trains are the confirmed automated systems for changing districts.'],
    ['Exploration inside a district','Once inside a district, players can move around freely. Most businesses have explorable interiors, which reduces the need to treat every shop doorway as a separate travel zone.'],
    ['Performance context','The team has been optimizing loading, memory and NPC materialization. Exact loading times depend on final hardware tests and should not be predicted from the existence of an SSD recommendation alone.']],round2Date],
  ['explorable-interiors','Can You Enter Buildings in Nivalis Nights?','How explorable business interiors work within Nivalis Nights districts.','Yes. The developer says players can freely explore each district, including the interiors of most businesses that make the city feel alive.',[
    ['Most, not every building','The wording confirms broad interior access but does not promise that every visible building can be entered. Location guides should distinguish functional interiors from scenery after the final map is available.'],
    ['District structure','Large districts are separated by loading screens, while interiors are part of the freely explorable space inside them. New areas also unlock as the story progresses.'],
    ['Future location pages','Each business or building page needs an exact route, services, relevant characters, opening conditions and connected quests before indexing.']],round2Date],
  ['post-launch-support','Will Nivalis Nights Get Post-Launch Updates?','What ION LANDS has said about updates, feedback and ongoing support after release.','Yes. ION LANDS says it plans to continue supporting Nivalis Nights after release, particularly by improving the game in response to player feedback and suggestions.',[
    ['What is promised','The commitment is to ongoing support and improvement. It does not currently provide a dated DLC roadmap, named expansions or a guaranteed number of patches.'],
    ['How this wiki will track updates','Patch pages will record version, release date, official changes, affected guides and fixed issues. Speculative feature wish lists will remain separate from confirmed updates.'],
    ['Evergreen SEO value','Versioned troubleshooting and change histories become durable search assets only when old information is clearly tied to the patch where it applied.']],round2Date],
  ['open-world','Is Nivalis Nights Open World?','How the large district structure, transportation, interiors and story unlocks shape Nivalis Nights exploration.','Nivalis Nights is tagged Open World on Steam, but the developer describes a district-based city: large areas are freely explorable, with loading screens and automated travel between districts.',[
    ['Free exploration within districts','Players can enter most business interiors and move around each district freely. Boats open access to water-connected areas, while story progression unlocks additional locations.'],
    ['Not one seamless map','HOVA taxis and trains handle district changes, and the developer explicitly confirms loading screens between districts. “Open world” therefore should not be interpreted as a single seamless space.'],
    ['Story structure','The game also has a defined main story and specific ending. Open-ended business and life-sim activities exist alongside that directed narrative.']],round2Date],
  ['relationship-types','Nivalis Nights Relationship Types','The confirmed friendship, rivalry, business partnership and romance relationship paths.','Relationships with characters can develop as friendships, rivalries, business partnerships or romances, depending largely on dialogue choices and side-quest decisions.',[
    ['Four confirmed paths','ION LANDS names friendship, rivalry, business partnership and romance in its community Q&A. A character may react differently over time based on the player’s choices, goals and quest outcomes.'],
    ['Character depth','More than 130 characters are planned, each with a background, personality and goals. That does not mean every character supports all four relationship types.'],
    ['Guide standard','A leaf page will label a relationship route only after verification and will separate general affinity from romance eligibility. Choice consequences will carry spoiler warnings.']],round2Date],
  ['food-stall-guide','Nivalis Nights Food Stall Guide','How food stalls fit the starting business ladder before restaurants and nightclubs.','The official publisher description says players can start small with a food stall, noodle stand or stim store before building toward bars, restaurants and nightclubs.',[
    ['Early business role','Food stalls represent one of the confirmed small-scale starting points. Ingredient buying, greenhouse supply, recipe unlocks and kitchen inventory are the wider systems likely to determine how such a venue operates.'],
    ['What still needs testing','No official startup price, menu, capacity, staff limit or upgrade route has been published. The final guide must distinguish a generic food stall from the separately named noodle stand.'],
    ['Comparison method','Early venues will be compared using total setup cost, operating time, supply needs and repeatable profit rather than gross sales alone.']],round2Date],
  ['stim-store-guide','Nivalis Nights Stim Store Guide','What is officially known about operating a stim store in the Nivalis Nights business system.','A stim store is one of the small businesses named by 505 Games as a possible starting point, alongside food and noodle stands.',[
    ['Confirmed but not detailed','The publisher’s game page includes the stim store in the business ladder but does not explain its products, ingredients, licenses or relationship to restaurants. Those systems should not be borrowed from Cloudpunk or fan speculation.'],
    ['Why it deserves its own page','A non-food starting business may have different stock and customer mechanics from restaurants. That distinct search intent justifies a guide once release data is available.'],
    ['Publication gate','Exact inventory, prices, upgrades and profit will be added only from official information or reproducible play testing.']],round2Date],
  ['bar-guide','Nivalis Nights Bar Guide','How bars sit between small starting businesses, restaurants and high-end nightclubs.','Bars are included in the official publisher’s business progression, between early stands and larger restaurant or nightclub ownership.',[
    ['Business ladder','505 Games describes progression from food stalls, noodle stands and stim stores into bars, restaurants and nightclubs. Steam also mentions cocktails in earlier official materials connected to the same game.'],
    ['Separate from nightclubs','Bars and nightclubs are named as different venue types, so their menus, staffing and operating rules should not be merged without evidence.'],
    ['Launch guide fields','A complete bar page needs acquisition cost, drink recipes, ingredient supply, staff roles, opening hours, upgrades, capacity and tested profit.']],round2Date],
  ['skyhigh-gardens','Nivalis Nights Skyhigh Gardens District Guide','Confirmed landmarks, transport, businesses and visual design in the elevated Skyhigh Gardens district.','Skyhigh Gardens is an exclusive district above the city, reached by flying taxi. It combines hanging gardens and wooden bridges with neon businesses, Eastern-inspired architecture, torii gates and a Japanese restaurant.',[
    ['What makes the district distinct','ION LANDS introduced Skyhigh Gardens in its September 2025 community blog. Tall buildings and connected structures create high views over Nivalis, while quiet greenery contrasts with commercial signs and busy venues. The district is presented as attractive to residents and demanding tourists.'],
    ['Known landmarks and food','The official preview identifies well-tended hanging gardens, wooden bridges, torii gates and a Japanese restaurant serving sushi and noodles. No final street map, venue name, menu prices or property list has been published, so those details remain launch-day verification tasks.'],
    ['How to reach it','The developer says citizens use a flying taxi service to reach the gardens. The Metro Hub-centered subway handles most other city travel, but the preview does not confirm a normal rail stop inside Skyhigh Gardens.']],round3Date],
  ['calypso-island','Nivalis Nights Calypso Island Guide','What is officially confirmed about Calypso Island, its housing and its place in the wider city.','Calypso Island is a warmer part of Nivalis where players can rent or acquire a standalone house. Official previews distinguish its island atmosphere from elevated Skyhigh Gardens, but a complete map and service list are not public yet.',[
    ['Confirmed island identity','The developer’s community updates refer to the warm Calypso Island as a previously explored district or area of the city. It is connected to the water-oriented side of Nivalis and is distinct enough to support its own housing style.'],
    ['Housing on Calypso Island','ION LANDS specifically names a standalone house on Calypso Island as an alternative to studio apartments and lofts. The final rent, purchase conditions, storage, furnishing and transport route have not been disclosed.'],
    ['Guide publication plan','After release, this page will add the island route, docks or stations, businesses, residents, quests, fishing access and available properties. It will not import locations from Cloudpunk merely because both games use the same city.']],round3Date],
  ['metro-hub','Nivalis Nights Metro Hub Guide','What The Metro Hub does and how it connects the city subway network.','The Metro Hub is the named center of Nivalis’s intricate subway system. ION LANDS says the subway will be sufficient for most journeys, while special areas such as Skyhigh Gardens use other transport.',[
    ['Role in city travel','The September 2025 district preview identifies The Metro Hub as the center of the subway network. This makes it a transport landmark rather than proof that every district connects through a single direct train.'],
    ['Metro versus special transport','Most travel can use the subway, but Skyhigh Gardens requires the flying taxi service described in the same update. Players can also use HOVA taxis between districts and pilot a boat on waterways.'],
    ['Details still to verify','Official materials have not published the final line map, fares, schedules, station entrances or transfer rules. The release guide will document exact routes and loading transitions from the shipped build.']],round3Date],
  ['flying-taxi','Nivalis Nights Flying Taxi Guide','How the flying taxi service provides access to Skyhigh Gardens.','A flying taxi is the confirmed service used to reach the elevated Skyhigh Gardens district. It is described separately from HOVA taxis, trains and the player-controlled boat.',[
    ['Confirmed purpose','ION LANDS says citizens need the flying taxi service to reach the gardens in the sky. The statement establishes a specific transport requirement but does not reveal the pickup point, fare, unlock quest or travel time.'],
    ['Do not confuse transport types','The broader Q&A names automated HOVA taxis and trains for movement between districts. The Skyhigh preview uses the distinct phrase “flying taxi service,” so this guide keeps that route separate until the final interface shows how the services relate.'],
    ['Launch-day checks','A verified walkthrough will identify terminals, destination choices, cost, availability by time of day and whether story or business progress gates access. Pre-release screenshots cannot establish those operating details.']],round3Date],
  ['skyhigh-japanese-restaurant','Skyhigh Gardens Japanese Restaurant Guide','Confirmed food, setting and business context for the Japanese restaurant in Skyhigh Gardens.','Skyhigh Gardens includes a Japanese restaurant overlooking the clouds where sushi and noodles are served. The player may visit it while observing competing businesses, but its final name and management status are not confirmed.',[
    ['Food and setting','The official district preview mentions fresh sushi and steaming noodles at a Japanese restaurant with a view of the clouds. Wooden bridges, torii gates and Eastern-inspired design reinforce the surrounding district identity.'],
    ['Competitor context','ION LANDS suggests the visit can help the player scope out competitors. That wording supports a business connection, but it does not prove that this exact restaurant can be purchased, sabotaged or operated.'],
    ['Missing launch details','The venue name, menu, opening hours, owner, quests and prices are not public. This page will remain a confirmed location overview until those fields can be tested in the release build.']],round3Date],
  ['apartment-rental','How Apartment Rental Works in Nivalis Nights','Confirmed rental limits, locations and furnishing rules for apartments across Nivalis.','Players can rent apartments in different parts of the city and may rent as many as their wallet permits. A strategically located home can make travel around Nivalis more convenient.',[
    ['No announced fixed property limit','The August 2025 housing preview ties the number of rentals to available money rather than naming a hard cap. This does not reveal deposits, recurring rent, eviction rules or whether every residence uses the same contract.'],
    ['Location has practical value','The developer explicitly says a home in a strategic location can improve movement around the city. That matters in a district-based map where travel can involve HOVA taxis, trains and loading screens.'],
    ['What tenants can change','Some rentals include basic furniture, and players can place furniture and decorations to personalize apartments. Exact storage limits, fast-travel behavior and whether furnishings persist after ending a rental require final-game testing.']],round3Date],
  ['apartment-types','Nivalis Nights Apartment and House Types','The confirmed studio, loft and standalone house options for player housing.','Official housing information names three scales of home: a minimal studio apartment, a cozy loft and a standalone house on Calypso Island. Different city districts also have their own styles.',[
    ['Studio apartments','A studio is the smallest housing example named by ION LANDS. The preview does not provide floor area, room count, rent or furniture capacity, so “minimal” should not be converted into unsupported numerical comparisons.'],
    ['Lofts and standalone houses','Lofts provide a middle example, while the Calypso Island house represents a separate residential building. The Q&A also confirms apartments and standalone houses across multiple districts as property types players can obtain.'],
    ['How to compare homes at launch','Useful comparisons should measure total cost, usable placement space, storage, nearby transport and services. Visual size alone is not enough to declare a best home, especially when location changes travel convenience.']],round3Date],
  ['home-location-strategy','Best Home Location Factors in Nivalis Nights','How to evaluate housing locations using travel, district access and cost without inventing a pre-release best apartment.','There is no verified best home before release. ION LANDS confirms that strategic apartment locations can make city travel easier, so transport access, nearby activities and rent should drive comparisons.',[
    ['Travel is the first confirmed factor','Nivalis uses large districts with loading screens between them. HOVA taxis, trains, a Metro Hub and special flying taxi access make proximity to useful connections a practical consideration.'],
    ['Match housing to daily activity','A player focusing on restaurants may value a home near venues or ingredient vendors, while quest progression may shift activity to newly unlocked districts. Those are evaluation criteria, not confirmed bonuses or fast-travel rules.'],
    ['Comparison standard','At launch, recommendations will record rent, route time, loading transitions, nearby vendors, business access and furnishing space. A beautiful view will be treated separately from measurable convenience.']],round3Date],
  ['furniture-vendors','Nivalis Nights Furniture Vendors Guide','How furniture shops differ and what players can buy for apartments and venues.','Furniture and accessory vendors are distributed around the city, and each offers a distinct assortment. Players use their stock to decorate homes and business venues.',[
    ['Why multiple vendors matter','The housing preview says different vendors carry unique assortments rather than one universal catalog. That creates a reason to visit districts and compare stock when building a particular room style.'],
    ['Furniture scope','The May 2026 optimization update reports 620 furniture items in the game. The count supports a large catalog, but does not publish shop inventories, prices or unlock requirements for individual pieces.'],
    ['Vendor page standard','After release, each vendor entry should list exact location, hours, stock categories, prices, material sets and prerequisites. Rotating inventory should be distinguished from permanent stock through repeated observations.']],round3Date],
  ['furniture-materials','Nivalis Nights Furniture Materials and Sets','What official housing previews reveal about furniture sets, accessories and material-based styles.','Furniture vendors sell sets distinguished by different materials, allowing apartments and venues to take on different visual atmospheres. Exact material names and complete set lists are not public yet.',[
    ['Materials shape style','ION LANDS describes each furniture set as having different materials that change the atmosphere of a home. The wording confirms stylistic groups, not crafting recipes or stat bonuses.'],
    ['Where sets can be used','Players can place furniture and decorations in apartments as well as business venues. Some homes begin with basic furnishing, which can then be customized with items found around the city.'],
    ['Database rules','A material or set page will be indexed only after its official in-game name, included items and acquisition source are verified. Color swaps will stay grouped when separate URLs would not provide different answers.']],round3Date],
  ['interior-design-jobs','Nivalis Nights Interior Design Jobs Guide','How paid client decorating works, including instructions, taste and completion requirements.','Players can accept paid interior-design work from people around the city. Unlike decorating their own homes, client jobs require following instructions, matching the client’s taste and satisfying specific requirements.',[
    ['How jobs are found','The August 2025 community blog says potential clients can be encountered in the streets. They are willing to pay someone who can improve their home, but the developer has not disclosed a job board, skill threshold or fixed contact method.'],
    ['Creative freedom has constraints','Personal apartments allow broad aesthetic freedom. Client spaces add a challenge because the finished design must respect stated taste and furnishing requirements rather than only the player’s preferred style.'],
    ['What a walkthrough must include','Each released job guide should record the client, starting location, budget, mandatory items or materials, scoring conditions, payment and failure recovery. Unverified decoration guesses should not be presented as required solutions.']],round3Date],
  ['interior-design-requirements','How to Meet Interior Design Client Requirements','A pre-release framework for interpreting Nivalis Nights decorating instructions without inventing scoring rules.','Client decorating jobs have explicit instructions and requirements. The exact scoring interface is not yet public, so the safe approach is to separate mandatory constraints from the client’s broader aesthetic taste after release.',[
    ['Known job conditions','ION LANDS confirms three elements: clients pay for the work, provide instructions and expect furnishing that matches their taste. Completing requirements is tied to leaving the client satisfied.'],
    ['Do not assume a hidden score','The preview does not confirm star ratings, timed objectives, budget penalties or required percentages. Those familiar housing-game mechanics cannot be attributed to Nivalis Nights without final evidence.'],
    ['Release checklist','A tested guide will capture the original brief, room boundaries, required categories, accepted alternatives and completion trigger. It will also note whether moving existing furniture affects the result or payment.']],round3Date],
  ['vendors','Nivalis Nights Vendors Guide','Confirmed vendor categories, district distribution, inventories and relationship effects.','Vendors operate across multiple districts and sell goods ranging from cooking ingredients to furniture. Repeated business with certain vendors may improve prices through the relationship system.',[
    ['Broad inventory categories','The community Q&A confirms that vendors around the city cover both operational supplies and home decoration. Greenhouse machinery and seeds are also described as purchases from specialized sellers in an earlier development update.'],
    ['Vendors connect systems','A vendor can influence restaurant supply, greenhouse setup, furniture collection and the economy. Multiple inventories mean purchases may belong in personal, kitchen, greenhouse or home storage depending on their use.'],
    ['Future directory fields','Each named vendor page needs district, route, hours, permanent or rotating stock, prices, relationship effects and connected quests. A generic shop sign is not enough evidence for an entity page.']],round3Date],
  ['vendor-discounts','How Vendor Discounts Work in Nivalis Nights','What is confirmed about earning better vendor prices through repeated purchases and business relationships.','Buying regularly from certain vendors may lead to better prices. ION LANDS presents this as an example of how business relationships can affect the player economically, not as a universal guaranteed discount.',[
    ['The official wording is conditional','The developer says buying more often from certain vendors “might” get better prices. That leaves room for vendor-specific rules, relationship thresholds or story choices rather than one global loyalty meter.'],
    ['Discounts versus cheap items','A lower observed price does not prove a relationship discount because market events can also change behavior. Release testing should compare the same item, vendor and market conditions over time.'],
    ['Verification method','A reliable guide will record purchase count, dialogue changes, relationship state, base price and discounted price. It will also test whether discounts expire, stack or apply to every product category.']],round3Date],
  ['business-partnerships','Nivalis Nights Business Partnerships Guide','How business partnerships fit the relationship system and can create economic opportunities.','Business partnership is one of four confirmed relationship paths. These relationships can change the economic experience and open opportunities, although named partners and benefits are not public before release.',[
    ['A distinct relationship type','The Q&A lists business partnerships alongside friendship, rivalry and romance. This means economic cooperation is not merely a generic friendship label, but not every character is confirmed to support it.'],
    ['Possible effects, careful limits','ION LANDS confirms economic impact and new opportunities, with vendor pricing as one example. It does not promise shared ownership, passive income, exclusive stock or loans, so those possibilities remain speculation.'],
    ['Guide evidence standard','Partner pages will document prerequisites, dialogue or quest choices, benefits, conflicts and reversibility. Economic claims must be reproduced or directly sourced, especially when market events could change prices.']],round3Date],
  ['market-events','Nivalis Nights Market Events Guide','How city events can affect market behavior and the evidence needed for price tracking.','Certain events can change how some markets behave. Watching those events can help players make better economic decisions, but the developers have not yet named event types, affected goods or price ranges.',[
    ['Confirmed economic variation','The community Q&A directly connects some events to market behavior. This suggests that buying and selling decisions may depend on world state rather than only fixed price lists.'],
    ['Avoid invented trading advice','There is no official commodity chart, event calendar or guaranteed buy-low strategy. Vendor discounts and market movement must also be separated because relationships can independently affect prices.'],
    ['Launch tracking method','The finished guide will record event name, start and end conditions, affected markets, baseline prices and observed changes. Multiple samples are needed before presenting a pattern as repeatable.']],round3Date],
  ['day-night-opportunities','Nivalis Nights Day and Night Opportunities','How the day/night cycle changes available activities and interacts with curfew.','Day and night offer different opportunities in Nivalis Nights, and curfew is one reason their activities differ. Exact schedules and night-only events are not fully published.',[
    ['Gameplay impact is confirmed','ION LANDS says the day/night system directly affects gameplay rather than serving only as lighting. Time therefore matters when planning quests, shopping, relationships and business activity.'],
    ['Night is not simply extra daytime','Curfew creates rules and risks after dark, while official marketing also connects illegal competitor sabotage to curfew. This does not establish the precise hours, penalties or every activity available at night.'],
    ['Schedule guide plan','After release, district tables will record vendor hours, character schedules, transport access, quest windows and curfew boundaries. Recommendations will state whether an opportunity is time-gated or merely easier at a certain hour.']],round3Date],
  ['relationship-story-effects','How Relationships Affect the Nivalis Nights Story','How NPC relationships change the route to fixed story endings and side-quest outcomes.','Relationships can influence how players reach the main story’s intended endings and can change side-quest outcomes. They do not mean the game has no defined narrative destination.',[
    ['Fixed endings, different paths','ION LANDS says the game has specific endings it wants players to reach, while choices and relationships alter the path. This supports route variation without claiming an unlimited number of finales.'],
    ['Side quests react to choices','More than 130 characters have goals, backgrounds and personalities. Interaction choices can lead to different dialogue and outcomes in their connected side quests.'],
    ['Spoiler-safe documentation','Character and quest pages will label the decision point before hiding consequences behind spoilers. A relationship effect must be tied to a verified choice, quest state or dialogue outcome rather than inferred from tone.']],round3Date],
  ['relationship-economy','How Relationships Affect the Nivalis Nights Economy','Confirmed economic effects from vendors and business relationships.','Relationships are not purely narrative: business connections can affect the economy and unlock opportunities. Repeated purchases from certain vendors may produce better prices.',[
    ['Economic relationship layer','The developer’s Q&A explicitly answers that relationships can influence gameplay. It separates business effects from the story and side-quest outcomes caused by other character interactions.'],
    ['Two variables can change price','Vendor loyalty may lower prices, while world events can alter market behavior. Testing must control for both before assigning a saving to one relationship choice.'],
    ['What guides will calculate','Release guides will compare prerequisites, purchase history, price changes and opportunity value. They will avoid labeling a relationship “best” unless its benefits are measured against lost alternatives and story consequences.']],round3Date],
  ['district-business-strategy','Nivalis Nights District Business Expansion Strategy','How to evaluate expansion across districts using property, staff, supply and travel constraints.','Players can acquire venues across different districts, but no official best expansion order exists before launch. A sound comparison must include setup cost, supply logistics, staffing, transport and local opportunities.',[
    ['Expansion is confirmed','The community Q&A says players can purchase multiple restaurants or venues and expand business into new districts. Story progress also unlocks additional locations to explore.'],
    ['Districts create operational differences','Large districts are separated by loading travel, while staff and persistent world systems continue in the background. Greenhouses, kitchens and vendors can also place supplies in different inventories and locations.'],
    ['How routes will be ranked','Launch recommendations will compare total investment, repeatable profit, travel time, vendor access and management burden. Tourist appeal or visual prestige, including Skyhigh Gardens, will not be treated as a profit bonus without evidence.']],round3Date],
  ['fishing-spots-species','Nivalis Nights Fishing Spots and Species','How boat progression opens new fishing locations and species, plus the future database standard.','Fishing expands as the player progresses: using a boat can reveal new spots and fish species. Exact location and species names still require final-game verification.',[
    ['Physical fish simulation','Fish are not abstract random rolls. The developer says each fish has a physical representation, can follow other fish or bait and forms simulated shoals; the fish caught is the one visible in the water.'],
    ['Why the boat matters','The Q&A says fishing expands over time and specifically connects the player’s boat with discovering additional spots and species. It does not publish an upgrade order, bait list or guaranteed catches.'],
    ['Location page requirements','Every species guide will need a confirmed name, water location, access route, conditions, bait response, value and use. Screenshots alone will not establish rarity or spawn rules.']],round3Date],
  ['furniture-shopping','Nivalis Nights Furniture Shopping Guide','How to plan furniture purchases across vendors for homes, venues and client projects.','Furniture shopping requires visiting different city vendors because each carries a unique assortment. Purchases can furnish personal homes and business venues, while client jobs add taste and requirement constraints.',[
    ['Start with the destination','Personal decorating emphasizes the player’s style, but paid interior-design work follows a client brief. The same attractive item may therefore be useful in one space and irrelevant to another requirement.'],
    ['Catalog scale and variation','The developer reports 620 furniture items and describes sets distinguished by materials. That is enough to support filters and collection guides after release, not enough to publish invented item pages now.'],
    ['Practical buying checklist','A release shopping guide should compare price, vendor location, item dimensions, placement category, material set and storage destination. It should also verify return, resale and duplicate-purchase rules before recommending bulk buying.']],round3Date]
);

